      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TIPSY MISS (4) resumes from a spell of three-and-a-half months. Could only manage to finish seventh at the latest run over 1400m at Tamworth. Looks the one to beat in this grade after placing on debut at Scone. PERASTA (9) is back after a break of five-and-a-half months. Started the last campaign in good style when in the placings over 1100m at Gulargambone. One of the genuine hopes who gets map favours from the inside gate. AIRFIELD (5) last appeared four weeks ago when eighth over 1100m at Nowra on a heavy (9) surface. This is his first run for the Jacob Perrett stable and can return to form in a winnable contest. LOST FLOWERS (3) is a three-year-old filly by Casino Prince from Sound Sleuth on debut for the Gavin Groth yard. Hardly set the world alight at the trials but finds a very weak contest.",
